ù opere dell'autore; lo si può anche considerare uno dei principali protagonisti nel dibattito su Dante nel Cinquecento italiano.  aThis volume studies the profile of one of the most important figures of sixteenth-century Florence, Giovan Battista Gelli, highlighting some less studied aspects generally believed to be marginal in the context of his work. Not only was Gelli deeply interested in figurative art, attested in several works of his, he can also be considered one of the protagonists of the vivid sixteenth-century debates on Dante.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aCinquecento. 4aDante Alighieri. 4aGelli, Giovan Battista. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aCinquecento.  aDante Alighieri.  aGiovan Battista Gelli.  aRenaissance.2 aDeutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831110804990 cprintz978311108005540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111080130zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111080130zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111080130/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023  aZDB-23-GOA